2 unit Scallions
13.4 ounce Black Beans
1 unit Tex-Mex Paste
½ cup Mexican Cheese Blend
6 unit Flour Tortillas
1 unit Poblano Pepper
1 tablespoon Southwest Spice Blend
½ cup White Cheddar Cheese
2 tablespoon Smoky Red Pepper Crema
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil

• Wash and dry all produce.
• Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from
greens. Halve, core, and thinly slice poblano crosswise
into strips.

• Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring, until softened,
5-6 minutes. TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help
poblano soften.

• While poblano cooks, drain and rinse beans.
• Once poblano is softened, stir in scallion whites and
2 tsp Southwest Spice (4 tsp for 4 servings). (Be sure to
measure the Southwest Spice—we sent more.) Cook until
fragrant, 30 seconds.
• Add beans, Tex-Mex paste, and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4).
Cook, stirring, until filling is combined and thickened,
2-3 minutes.

• Sprinkle black bean filling with white cheddar and
Mexican cheese. Cover pan until cheese melts,
1-2 minutes. Turn off heat.
• Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels and microwave until
warm and pliable, 30 seconds.
• Divide tortillas between plates and fill with black bean
filling, smoky red pepper crema, and scallion greens.
Serve.